# Component Reuse Gate

**Blocker:** Do not wire new templates, page sections, dialogs, or inline editors until this gate passes.

## 1. Search (mandatory, before HTML/TS)

1. Read `docs/specs/component/registry.md` and the matching `registry.*.supplement.md` slice.
2. `grep` / semantic-search for the **interaction pattern** (e.g. "inline edit", "rename", "confirm") — not only the feature folder name.
3. Read 1–2 existing usages in `apps/web/src/app/shared/` or the closest feature.

## 2. Pattern quick reference

| Need | Reuse first |
| --- | --- |
| Inline title / text edit | `app-pane-header`, `app-media-detail-header` |
| Click-to-edit metadata row | `app-media-detail-inline-section`, `app-metadata-section` |
| Irreversible / destructive confirm | `app-confirm-dialog`, `app-projects-confirm-dialog` |
| One-shot name prompt (create flow) | `app-text-input-dialog` |
| Toast / mutation feedback | `ToastService` + `app-toast-container` |
| Status badge | `app-chip` |
| Filter / sort / grouping toolbar | `app-filter-dropdown`, `app-sorting-controls`, `app-grouping-dropdown` |
| Floating details / side panel | Existing feature panel pattern + `docs/design/shell-layout-tokens.md` |

**Default:** Prefer **inline edit** over modal when the same pattern exists elsewhere (rename title, edit field in place).

## 3. Decision (state before coding)

Reply with one line:

- **Reuse:** `<selector>` (+ how inputs/outputs map), or
- **Gap:** `<missing variant>` → ask user before duplicating HTML or inventing a modal.

## 4. Optional skills (large UI work)

- `@design-audit` — before new layouts or composition plans
- `@implement-from-spec` — when a `docs/specs/` contract exists
- `@component-structure` — before creating a new Angular component file
